                  @{"Authors" link "Authors"}
                  @{"Copyright and liability" link "Copyright"}


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Introduction"

 MoMo is a combination of hard- and software and can be used to
 start programs controlled by the RS232 lines 'RI' and 'DCD'.
 
 When an incoming call is detected, a specified program will be
 launched. Then, MoMo monitors the data carrier signal from the
 modem, when this signal is off, another programm will be started.
 
 The number of incomings rings from the modem will be counted, if
 the limit is reached, another program will be started. 

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements"

 - AmigaOS 3.0 or higher

 - a free joystick port

 - @{"Interface" link "Interface"}
 
 - commodities.library, gadtools.library, gameport.device

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Interface"

 The interface connects the modem with the software via the joystick
 port. It can be built with some very ordinary electronic elements.
 It's very cheap and easy to solder.

 One interface can monitor one modem. To monitor two modems, another
 interface must be built and the lines from the joystick port must
 be soldered to both interfaces. Mind the maximum power charge of the
 Amiga's joystickport, it could be wise not to connect the both monitor
 LEDs.

 @{"Circuit diagram" system "SYS:Utilities/MultiView MoMo.IFF SCREEN"}

 Elements required for one interface:
 
 2x Standard silicon diode (100mA), e.g.. 1N4148
 2x Standard npn transistor, e.g. BC548B
 4x Resistor, 1/4 watts, 1kOhms
 2x Resistor, 1/4 watts, 15kOhms
 2x Resistor, 1/4 watts, 100kOhms
 2x LED, e.g. 5mm red
 1x ILD74 (Double opto coupler, can be replaced with two CNY17)
 
 Wiring schematic:
 
 
 RS-232 (Modem)                                 Joystick connection
                  +----------------+
 RI  -------------|                |------------ Back (2)
 GND -------------| MoMo-Interface |------------ Fire (6)
 DCD -------------|                |------------ +5V  (7)
                  |                |------------ GND  (8)
                  +----------------+
 
 RS-232
 
         25pol.   9pol
 ------+-------+----------
 GND   |   7   |   5
 DCD   |   8   |   1
 RI    |  22   |   9

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Parameters"

 MoMo can be started either from the shell or the Workbench using an
 icon.
 
 These are the parameters:
 
 STARTPGM
 
 Name of the program to be started when an incoming call is detected:

 
 Ex.  ToolType: STARTPGM=RAM:StartHD
      Shell   : STARTPGM="RAM:StartHD"
      
 Default: "RAM:MoMo-HDStart"
 

 STOPPGM
 
 Name of the program to be started when the DCD signal is missing:
 
 Ex.  ToolType: STOPPGM=RAM:StopHD
      Shell   : STOPPGM="RAM:StopHD"
      
 Default: "RAM:MoMo-HD-Stop"
 
 
 RESETPGM
 
 Program to be started when the number of incoming calls exceeds the
 limit within 10 seconds.
 
 Ex.  ToolType: RESETPGM=RAM:Reboot
      Shell   : RESETPGM="RAM:Reboot"
      
 Default: "RAM:MoMo-Reset"
      

 HDSTATUS
 
 Defines the status of the radio buttons 'HD On' and 'HD Off'.
 
 Ex.  ToolType: HDSTATUS=O   (HD On)
                HDSTATUS=F   (HD Off)
      Shell   : HDSTATUS O   (HD On)
                HDSTATUS=F   (HD Off)
                
 Default: "O"


 AUTORESET
 
 Defines the status of the 'auto reset' check box.
 
 Ex.  ToolTypes: AUTORESET=YES
                 AUTORESET=NO
      Shell    : AUTORESET YES
                 AUTORESET NO
                 
 Default: "NO"
 
 
 RESETRINGS
 
 Maximum numbers of rings within 10 seconds.
 
 Ex.  ToolTypes: RESETRINGS=5
      Shell    : RESETRINGS 5
      
 Default: 8

      
 CX_POPUP
 
 Shows / hides the program interface after the start.
 
 Ex.  ToolTypes: CX_POPUP=YES
                 CX_POPUP=NO
      Shell    : CX_POPUP YES
                 CX_POPUP NO      
                 
 Default: "YES"
 

 CX_POPKEY
 
 Defines the hot key for this commodity.
 
 Ex.  ToolTypes: CX_POPKEY=ctrl alt r
      Shell    : CX_POPKEY="ctrl alt r"
      
 Default: "ctrl alt m"

@ENDNODE

